==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Blacktail
<hw>Black"tail`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Black</ets> + <ets>tail</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A fish; the ruff or pope.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The black-tailed deer
(<spn>Cervus Columbianus</spn> <it>or</it> <spn>Cariacus
Columbianus</spn>) of California and Oregon; also, the mule deer of the
Rocky Mountains. See <er>Mule deer</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blackthorn</ent>⟦br⟧
